parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause obstruction of the driver's vision, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down
does not stay in place
or flops down while driving
blocking the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window master switch can cause the windows to malfunction, leading to safety hazards and inconvenience.
symptoms: The power window master switch fails to operate
causing the windows to not roll up or down properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting of the dashboard can cause a safety hazard due to the reflective surface, which can distract the driver and cause accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard melts
causing a shiny
mirror-like surface that reflects sunlight and glares on the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents or near-misses, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to operate properly
causing the vehicle to not stop or slow down as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump and belts can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and safety hazards.
symptoms: The water pump and belts fail
causing engine damage and overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shattering of the rear window can cause safety hazards, such as obstructed vision and injuries from broken glass.
symptoms: The rear window shatters suddenly
causing damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting and sticky dashboard can cause a glare on the windshield, which can impair the driver's visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The dashboard is sticky to the touch
has a shiny or reflective surface
and may have cracks or melted areas. The glare from the dashboard can make it difficult to see the road
especially during sunny conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Sudden Loss of Braking Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to respond to braking inputs can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle does not stop when the brake pedal is pressed
the "Check VSC System" warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Check VSC System" warning light illuminates

the ABS light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle does not stop when the brake pedal is pressed.

symptoms: The "Check VSC System" warning light illuminates
the brake light illuminates
the ABS light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle does not stop when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also lead to reduced gas mileage and increased emissions.
symptoms: The vehicle burns excessive amounts of oil
requiring frequent oil additions
leading to a decrease in oil levels
and potentially causing engine failure.
